 commutes, so that for m\in  Gz, f^*m = fm \in  Gz'. Thus the disjoint
  union of the Gz is a sieve. Conversely, given a sieve S, we
  define Gz = \{z\xrightarrow {m} x\in  C(z, x)\}, with action on morphisms by
  pre-composition.

The universal property of the coproduct P =   \coprod _{j\in  J} X_j with coprojections X_k\xrightarrow {\iota _k} P is that, for any
  object Z equipped with morphisms X_k\xrightarrow {\kappa _k} Z, there exists a unique
  morphism P\to  Z making the following diagrams commute:




    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
